Galaxy Cablevision L.P. said itsigned a letter of intent to sell the assets of its cabletelevision systems in West Texas which serve about 4,600 basicsubscribers through nine cable television systems.    Terms were not disclosed and the Galaxy did not identifythe buyer. The company also said it will make its first cashdividend of 37 cents per unit on or about August 15 to holdersof record June 30.    In March, Galaxy completed a public offering of 2.2 mlnunits for 43 mln dlrs and acquired the assets of 132 cabletelevision systems for about 34 mln dlrs. Reuter&#3;